  <section id="etymology">
    <h>etymology</h>
    <p>The modern Gaelic preposition is a fusion of three different Old Gaelic prepositions – <ul>
        <li>the leniting, accusative/dative-governing preposition <ax href="https://dil.ie/3902"
            >ar</ax>
          <en>in front of, for (the sake of), on account of</en></li>
        <li>the non-mutating, accusative/dative-governing preposition <ax
            href="https://dil.ie/23272">for</ax>
          <en>on, over</en></li>
        <li>the nasalising, dative-governing preposition <ax href="https://dil.ie/26931">íar</ax>
          <en>after (temporal), according to</en></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </section>

